  "abstract": "Groundnut Bud Necrosis Disease (GBND) caused by Groundnut Bud Necrosis Virus (GBNV) has been considered as one of the major virus diseases in Andhra Pradesh. Survey conducted in groundnut growing areas of Anantapur district during kharif and rabi 2013-14 and in Karimnagar and Warangal districts during rabi 2013-14 season revealed the natural occurrence of GBND in different mandals with an overall average incidence of 3.47 per cent. Higher incidence of GBND was observed in Anantapur (8.50 per cent) followed by\r\nKarimnagar (0.97 per cent) and Warangal (0.94 per cent) districts. Groundnut cultivar K-6 was grown extensively in all the districts surveyed. The infected groundnut leaf samples collected from Anantapur district tested positive when subjected to DAC-ELISA",
